r%20to%20absorb%20the%20higher%20wages%20because%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcdonalds-california-menu-could-become-unaffordable-to-cover-wage-hike-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecustomers%20wouldn't%20come%20back%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScott%20Rodrick%2C%20who%20owns%2018%20McDonald's%20in%20northern%20California%2C%20told%20BI%20he%20had%20a%20%26quot%3Bdeep%20concern%26quot%3B%20that%20the%20new%20minimum%20wage%20%26quot%3Bnarrows%20the%20competitive%20gap%26quot%3B%20between%20different%20types%20of%20restaurants.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERodrick%20said%20he'd%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-mcdonalds-fast-food-20-minimum-wage-franchisee-cutting-costs-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincreased%20prices%20at%20his%20restaurants%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20between%205%25%20and%207%25%20in%20the%20three%20months%20of%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExecutives%20at%20Kura%20Sushi%2C%20a%20sit-down%20Japanese%20chain%20with%20about%2060%20locations%20in%20the%20US%2C%20told%20analysts%20in%20early%20April%20that%20they%20thought%20the%20%2420%20wage%20would%20increase%20their%20value%20proposition%20as%20other%20chains%20keep%20increasing%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECEO%20Hajime%20Uba%20noted%20that%20Kura%20Sushi's%20prices%20were%20getting%20%26quot%3Bcloser%20and%20closer%20and%20closer%26quot%3B%20to%20fast-food%20pricing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDiners%20generally%20go%20to%20fast-food%20and%20casual%20dining%20restaurants%20for%20different%20occasions%2C%20Brian%20Vaccaro%2C%20a%20restaurant%20analyst%20at%20Raymond%20James%2C%20told%20BI.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESit-down%20restaurants%20typically%20attract%20diners%20who%20want%20to%20%26quot%3Brelax%20and%20rewind%26quot%3B%20with%20family%20and%20friends.%20In%20contrast%2C%20people%20generally%20go%20to%20limited-service%20restaurants%20for%20the%20speed%20and%20convenience%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWages%20c