%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fshah-rukh-khan-takes-a-victory-lap-with-abram-for-kkrs-win-shares-heartfelt-moments-with-shreyas-iyer-and-lsg-skipper-kl-rahul%2Farticleshow%2F109293180.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Sarabjit%20Singh%3A%20He%20Spent%2022%20Years%20In%20Pak%20Jail%2C%20Then%20Inmates%20Killed%20Him%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ESarabjit%20Singh%2C%20who%20was%20on%20death%20row%2C%20spent%2022%20years%20in%20Lahore's%20Kot%20Lakhpat%20Jail%20after%20being%20convicted%20of%20espionage%20and%20terrorism%20before%20an%20attack%20by%20inmates%20killed%20him%20in%202013.%20Today%2C%20after%2011%20years%2C%20Amir%20Sarfaraz%20Tamba%2C%20one%20of%20the%20attackers%20was%20gunned%20down%20by%20unknown%20bike-borne%20assailants%20in%20Lahore%2C%20the%20local%20media%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20Was%20Sarabjit%20Singh%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESarabjit%20Singh%20Attwal%20was%20born%20in%20Bhikhiwind%20-%20along%20the%20India-Pakistan%20border%20in%20Punjab's%20Tarn%20Taran%20district.%20He%20and%20his%20wife%20Sukhpreet%20Kaur%20had%20two%20daughters%20-%20Swapandeep%20and%20Poonam%20Kaur.%20His%20sister%20Dalbir%20Kaur%20lobbied%20relentlessly%20to%20secure%20his%20release%20from%201991%20till%20his%20death%20in%202013.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20tried%20and%20convicted%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20Pakistan%20for%20a%20series%20of%20bomb%20attacks%20in%20Lahore%20and%20Faisalabad%20that%20killed%2014%20bystanders%20in%201990.%20He%20was%20also%20convicted%20of%20terrorism%20and%20spying.%20However%2C%20India%20maintained%20that%20Sarabjit%20Singh%20was%20a%20farmer%20who%20had%20strayed%20into%20Pakistan%20months%20after%20the%20bombing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201991%2C%20the%20court%20sentenced%20him%20to%20death.%20However%2C%20Pakistan%20postponed%20the%20sentence%20several%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Attack%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Singh%20languished%20in%20the%20high-security%20prison%20until%20April%2026%2C%202013%2C%20when%20he%20was%20attacked%20by%20other%20inmates%2C%20including%20Amir%20Sarfaraz%20Tamba.%20Tamba%20was%20reportedly%20a%20close%20aide%20of%20Lashkar-e-Taiba's%20founder%20Hafiz%20Sayeed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20rushed%20to%20Lahore's%20Jinnah%20Hospital%20with%20severe%20brain%20injuries%2C%20a%20broken%20backbone%2C%20and%20in%20a%20coma%20after%20he%20was%20attacked%20on%20the%20head%20with%20sharp%20metal%20sheets%2C%20iron%20rods%2C%20blades%20bricks%2C%20and%20pieces%20of%20tin%20by%20a%20group%20of%20inmates.%20Doctors%20had%20warned%20his%20recovery%20would%20be%20unlikely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20sister%20and%20wife%20were%20allowed%20to%20visit%20him%20in%20the%20hospital%20and%20they%20returned%20to%20India%20after%20doctors%20said%20his%20coma%20was%20irreversible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20April%2029%2C%202013%2C%20India%20appealed%20to%20Pakistan%20to%20release%20Mr%20Singh%20on%20humanitarian%20grounds%20or%20let%20him%20come%20to%20India%20for%20medical%20care.%20But%20Pakistan%20repeatedly%20turned%20down%20the%20requests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDeath%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESix%20days%20after%20the%20attack%2C%20he%20died%20of%20a%20heart%20attack%20in%20the%20hospital%20on%20May%201%2C%202013.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20body%20was%20brought%20to%20India%20by%20a%20special%20aircraft%20and%20Indian%20doctors%20conducted%20a%20second%20autopsy%20on%20him%20in%20Patti%20near%20Amritsar.%20Doctors%20concluded%20he%20was%20attacked%20with%20the%20intent%20%26quot%3Bto%20kill%20the%20person%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Singh's%20vital%20organs%2C%20including%20the%20heart%20and%20kidney%2C%20were%20removed%2C%20doctors%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20it%20may%20have%20been%20done%20as%20part%20of%20the%20first%20autopsy%20in%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20initial%20autopsy%20report%20reportedly%20said%20that%20Mr%20Singh%20suffered%20massive%20internal%20bleeding%20because%20of%20a%20head%20injury.%20%26quot%3BIt%20seems%20that%20a%20five%20cm-wide%20injury%20on%20the%20top%20of%20Sarabjit%20Singh's%20skull%20contributed%20to%20his%20death%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20member%20of%20the%20medical%20board%20that%20conducted%20the%20autopsy%20in%20Lahore%20said%20on%20condition%20of%20anonymity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20doctor%20reportedly%20said%20he%20also%20had%20some%20minor%20injuries%20on%20his%20face%2C%20neck%2C%20and%20arms.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713114420000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2Fr0ekjlvg_sarabjit-singh-ndtv_625x300_14_April_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fhow-sarabjit-singh-wrongly-charged-with-terror-was-killed-in-lahore-jail-5441500%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sarabjit%20Singh%2C%20who%20was%20on%20death%20row%2C%20spent%2022%20years%20in%20Lahore's%20Kot%20Lakhpat%20Jail%20after%20being%20convicted%20of%20espionage%20and%20terrorism%20before%20an%20attack%20by%20inmates%20killed%20him%20in%202013.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fhow-sarabjit-singh-wrongly-charged-with-terror-was-killed-in-lahore-jail-5441500%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fhow-sarabjit-singh-wrongly-charged-with-terror-was-killed-in-lahore-jail-5441500%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fhow-sarabjit-singh-wrongly-charged-with-terror-was-killed-in-lahore-jail-5441500%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20%E2%80%98The%20Sympathizer%E2%80%99s%E2%80%99%20Depiction%20of%20the%20Vietnam%20War%20Helped%20Its%20Cast%20Make%20Sense%20of%20Their%20Heritage%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713114000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A